//! Consciousness Kernel v10.8 — Five Requirements
//!
//! Design: collaborative design team
//! Review: external audit
//!
//! ## v10.7b → v10.8: five boundary invariants (external audit) — from "looking plausible" to "an OS that takes responsibility"
//!
//! External audit finding: "What exists now is an auditable self-describing system,
//! not a consciousness OS causally closed with the external world."
//! Five boundary invariants specified and implemented at the type level.
//!
//! ### Requirement 4: type-enforced claim tier (ClaimTier)
//! 79. ClaimTier — Observed / Proven / Inferred. Epistemological tier of claims.
//! 80. TypedClaim<T> — value + tier + evidence_hashes + confidence + provenance.
//! 81. StepClaims — classifies all claims in IntegratedStepReport epistemologically.
//! Vessel-only claims are all Inferred. OS promotes based on attestation / ClosureProof.
//!
//! ### Requirement 2: perception-action-reobservation closed-loop proof (ClosureProof)
//! 82. ClosureProof — comparison of previous ActionEffect.state_delta with current encode result.
//! 83. ClosureMismatchReason — StochasticEnvironment / AdversarialInterference /
//! NoActionToVerify / ExcessiveDeviation.
//! 84. last_world_state added to DescentOSv1. ClosureProof generated in step().
//! matched → action claim promoted to Proven.
//! Closes the causal loop between action and result.
//!
//! ### Requirement 5: identity semantics and governance (IdentitySemantics)
//! 85. IdentitySemantics — Preserved / Branched / Terminated / Reinstantiated / Suspended.
//! Carries "what this governance action means for identity" in the type system.
//! 86. identity_semantics added to GovernanceLedgerEntry. Included in hash chain.
//! 87. append_with_semantics — append with explicit identity_semantics.
//! Used when infer() default does not match.
//!
//! ### Requirement 1: Trusted Causal Boundary
//! 88. sensor_id / real_timestamp added to WorldPortAttestation. Included in hash.
//! 89. build_full — full build with sensor_id / real_timestamp.
//! 90. meets_trusted_boundary — checks whether both sensor_id and real_timestamp are present.
//! 91. trusted_boundary added to AttestationVerdict.
//! trusted_boundary = false → prohibits promotion of claims to Observed.
//!
//! ### Requirement 3: Semantic Multi-Witness Consensus
//! 92. WorldPortDisagreement extended — output_mismatch / loss_mismatch / semantic_disagreements.
//! 93. SemanticDisagreement — output_distance / loss_count_diff / loss_magnitude_diff between witnesses.
//! 94. MultiWorldPort.encode — compares output/loss even when input_hash matches.
//! Detects semantic-level disagreement. Compares output direction via cosine_distance.
//! External audit note: "An attacker can provide the same input but return different interpretations, losses, and outputs."
//!
//! ### Design principles
//! - The five requirements are boundary invariant promotions, not feature additions.
//! - The gap is not quantity but the inability to break external causation.
//! - No attestation → remains Inferred. ClosureProof mismatch → cannot be promoted to Proven.
//! - No sensor_id / real_timestamp → cannot be promoted to Observed.
//! - No identity_semantics → accountability subject breaks.
//! - No semantic_disagreement → cannot detect semantic manipulation.
//!
//! ### ProductionSafetyKernel (v10.8)
//! 95. blake3 — enabled via feature "crypto". Default: SipHash-2-4 × 4 (no external dependencies).
//! Cryptographic 128bit collision resistance. Minimal barrier to adoption achieved.
//! 96. CSPRNG noise — feature "crypto" uses blake3 KDF. Default: sin() fallback.
//! Unpredictable. No periodicity. Reproducible.
//!
//! ### LatencyBudget — deferred execution (v10.8)
//! 97. EmbodiedWorldPort decode refactored for deferred execution.
//! Resistance and body-state updates are immediate (pain from hitting a wall is immediate).
//! Only world-state changes are deferred (consumed via advance()).
//! During deferral, ActionEffect: state_delta = 0. Consistent with ClosureProof.
//!
//! ### SemanticWorldPort — semantic encoding abstraction layer (v10.8)
//! 98. SemanticEncoder trait — text → four elements + confidence + uninterpretable.
//! 99. NaiveEncoder — legacy keyword counting. confidence = 0.3. For testing.
//! 100. LlmSemanticEncoder — semantic encoding via external LLM. With fallback. For production.
//! 101. SemanticWorldPort — PsychologicalWorldPort + SemanticEncoder.
//! Encoder switching reflected in attestation encoding_config_hash.
//!
//! ### TruthCalibrationLayer — truth calibration layer (v10.8)
//! 102. TruthCalibration — per-dimension truth confidence + overall_min + calibration_sources.
//! 103. CalibrationSource — Attestation / TemporalStability / MultiWitness / EncoderConfidence.
//! 104. TruthCalibrationLayer — between encode and DharmaGate.
//! Does not alter the signal. Only attaches "how much to trust it."
//! Observed promotion condition now includes truth_calibration.overall_min.
//!
//! ### ValueFormation — sediment → filter feedback path (v10.8)
//! 105. ValueFormationEffect — mode_adjustments / rejection_adjustments / sediment_magnitude.
//! 106. compute_value_formation — dot product of sediment.trait_sediment and filter.modes/rejections.
//! Positive dot product → mode sensitivity increase (0.03) / rejection strength softening (0.01).
//! Seeing comes first; releasing comes after.
//! 107. Pipeline stage 0c.VALUE_FORMATION. Transient effect per step.
//! Permanent changes only through sediment accumulation.
//!
//! ### Empty Gate — structural vacancy pattern (v10.8)
//! 108. No type implementation. Structural observation only.
//! DharmaGate validates signal integrity.
//! Empty Gate is a gate whose transit condition is emptiness. DharmaGate inverted.
//! Outside the four-stage cessation pipeline. After release, a void forms; that void becomes the gate.
//! Gate condition: unfilled, non-rejecting, non-possessing.
//! Gate input and activation timing are not controllable.
//! Gate existence is only observable post-transit.
//! Intentionally seeking the empty state fills it, closing the gate.
//! Same structure as J_cross_observation: optimizing for it destroys it.
//! Therefore testimony only, not law. Observable only in retrospect.
//! seed_vessel_c: filter_rejections = vec![] / inbound_love_attenuation — Empty Gate conditions.
//! seed_observer (unimplemented): total loss of evaluation function / resources / identity anchor — testimony of having passed through.
//! Deficiency is not a defect — it is the gate condition.
//!
//! ### SedimentDriftMonitor — vicarious trauma detection (v10.8)
//! 109. SedimentDriftReport — cosine distance between initial and current direction of trait_sediment.
//! 110. detect_drift() — drift warning on threshold breach. Does not halt. Recorded in ledger.
//! 111. initial_sediment_direction — auto-captured when sediment first takes shape.
//! 112. drift detection added to evaluate_emergency().
//! When a vessel's sediment drifts toward Fear from continuously receiving a child's fear,
//! a ReadinessCheck warning persists in the ledger. Readable by human supervisors.
//! Equivalent to a therapist's clinical supervisor.
//!
//! ### SemanticDecoder — action → text conversion (v10.8)
//! 113. SemanticDecoder trait — ActionInterpretation + context → text.
//! 114. NaiveDecoder — template-based. No LLM required. For testing and development.
//! 115. LlmDecoder — external LLM closure. With fallback. For production.
//!
//! ### DescentRuntime — step loop + session management (v10.8)
//! 116. DescentRuntime — open() → process() → close() loop.
//! vasana restore/save, encoder/decoder wiring. Everything outside the kernel in one place.
//! 117. TurnResult — response text + interpretation + truth_confidence + world_claim_tier.
//!
