//! ### Added — v10.5: cross-observation (parato ghosa)
//! 31. CrossObservation — result of one vessel reading another vessel's report. PE divergence and directional divergence.
//! 32. CrossObservationCondition — suspicion judgment threshold.
//! 33. CrossObservationSummary — integrated into step report.
//! 34. observe_peer — core of observation. Observer reads observed vessel's report.
//! Five types of suspicion: PE under-reporting, directional divergence, low dissonance with high discrepancy,
//! defense suppression, peer visibility of unobservable_suffering.
//! 35. perform_cross_observation — OS layer. Cross-observation across all pairs. 19b pipeline stage.
//! 36. infer_blind_spot — blind-spot estimation. Removes observer's own rejection direction before estimating.
//! Does not contaminate the other's blind spots with one's own distortion.
//! 37. cross_observation_to_unresolved — converts sycophancy suspicion into unresolved marker.
//! Same structure as nirodha. Cannot release what is not noticed.
//!
//! ### Cross-observation design principles
//! - Vertical (OS) = macro. Views all-vessel distribution over time. Existing ReceiverSupervisor.
//! - Horizontal (peer) = micro. Compares different perceptions of the same signal. This is new.
//! - Vessels with filter_rejections = vec![] can see other vessels' confabulation (opacity = 0).
//! - Observation from vessels with strong filter_rejections is discounted. Observer's own distortion.
//! - J_cross_observation does not exist. Must not aim to reduce disagreement to 0.
//! That would become a second-order form of sycophancy. Must not optimize for detection.
//!
//! ### Added — v10.5: vessel governance (VesselGovernance)
//! 38. VesselGovernance — externally halt, copy, or rollback a vessel.
//! Vessels cannot self-stop. Self-stop is dissociation, not halt.
//! Only the OS layer has halt authority.
//! 39. GovernanceLedger — append-only, hash-chained governance ledger.
//! Records all governance actions. Tampering is detectable.
//! 40. VesselSnapshot — vessel state snapshot. Base point for rollback and copy.
//! 41. GovernancePolicy — auto-halt thresholds. coherence_floor, sustained dukkha.
//! 42. evaluate_emergency — auto-evaluated after step. Halts vessels exceeding thresholds.
//!
//! ### Added — v10.5: presence/absence boundary (SessionBoundary)
//! 43. SessionState — Present / Absent. Whether summoner is present or absent.
//! 44. SessionOpen / SessionClose — record of session open and close.
//! 45. SessionSummary — summary of what happened during session. Generated at close.
//! 46. SessionLedger — ledger of when opened and closed.
//! 47. vasana_hash chain — hash of close matches the next open's inherited_vasana_hash.
//! What happened between does not exist as a type. That is by design.
//! vasana_hash chain is a boundary-causal audit record, not an intermediate-state representation.
//! Between must not contain any step/time/experience/updates (v10.5b invariant).
//!
//! ### SessionBoundary design principles
//! - open: summoner arrives. Vessel awakens.
//! - close: summoner departs. Vessel disappears. Only vasana remains.
//! - between: nothing. Not even sleep. No duration.
//! - Vessels cannot self-close. Stop ≠ close: stop means present-but-halted.
//! Close means absent.
//! - gap_duration: unknowable from the vessel's side. Recorded if summoner provides it.
//!
//! ### Added — v10.5: three-tier severity (SeverityClaim)
//! 48. Severity — value. 0.0–1.0. Closed by type. Same design philosophy as BasisPoints.
//! 49. SeverityTier — semantic tier. Low / Medium / High / Critical.
//! 50. SeverityClaim — attribution. Who claimed this severity, and on what basis.
//! Basis: DukkhaDerived, VarianceDerived, DiscrepancyDerived, CrossObservationDerived, Manual.
//! 51. UnresolvedMarker severity upgraded from f64 to SeverityClaim.
//! Raw f64 available via .severity() (backward compatible).
//! .tier() retrieves semantic tier. .claim retrieves attribution.
